snippet.title: MahaShivRatri 2024 Livestream with Sadhguru @ Isha Yoga Center | 8 Mar, 6 PM
snippet.description:
Celebrate Mahashivratri 2024 with Sadhguru on 8 March 2024, starting at 6 PM IST/12:30 PM GMT.

Mahashivratri is one of the largest and most significant among the sacred festivals of India and a night of immense spiritual possibilities for any spiritual seeker.

Contribute towards Mahashivratri activities and Maha Annadanam (a sacred offering of food) to devotees during the auspicious time of Mahashivratri: https://sadhguru.co/annam

#Mahashivratri2024 #AwakeWithAdiyogi #Mahashivratri #Live #AdiyogiLive #SadhguruLive  

Those who wish to enhance their receptivity to the auspicious period of Mahashivratri can participate in Pancha Bhuta Kriya with Sadhguru. The online program takes place on 8 March, before Mahashivratri.
Register at https://sadhguru.co/pbk-yt

Rudraksha Diksha is an opportunity to bring home the grace of Adiyogi by receiving a Rudraksha powerfully energized by Sadhguru on Mahashivratri night.
 Register now:  https://sadhguru.co/rd

Yaksha - an exuberant festival of Classical Music & Dance by world-renowned artistes - will take place from 5-7 March.

Transform Your Life in 7 Steps With Sadhguru Register now: https://sadhguru.co/ie-yt

"The Sadhguru Podcast -  Of Mystics and Mistakes   (Listen Now on)"
https://open.spotify.com/show/69ZUhdV0q2JtibNU2yLTpQ

Get access to rare Sadhguru content on Sadhguru Exclusive. Choose from a variety of series that cover the mystical, intense, intimate and candid.
Watch Now: https://sadhguru.co/exclusive

Official YouTube Channel of Sadhguru

Considered among India‚Äôs 50 most influential people, Sadhguru is a yogi, mystic, bestselling author, and poet. Absolute clarity of perception places him in a unique space, not only in matters spiritual but in business, environmental and international affairs, and opens a new door on all that he touches.

Inner Engineering 

Inner Engineering is a comprehensive course for personal growth that brings about a shift in the way you perceive and experience your life, your work, and the world that you live in.

https://innerengineering.sadhguru.org/

Isha Life products for everyday health and well-being. Buy online at https://bit.ly/3L0gTar

Save Soil Movement

Launched by Sadhguru, Save Soil is the world's largest people's movement, reaching 3.91 billion people to address impending soil extinction by supporting governments to create policies for soil revitalization.

https://savesoil.org/

Sadhguru app 

Accelerate your spiritual journey with transformative guided meditations, daily wisdom, and Yogic tools.

http://onelink.to/sadhguru__app

Khumar Episode 31 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints - Feroze Khan - Neelam Muneer - 8th March 2024 - Har Pal Geo

Khumar Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints

Khumar is a timeless love story that delves into the challenges arising from societal class differences and the negativity that stems from them. Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.

Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from a
lower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.

Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.

What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? If they marry, can they create a happy life together despite their different backgrounds and mindsets?

snippet.description:
Click here to subscribe to Sony LIV Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/sonyliv
 
Click here to watch all highlights: https://bit.ly/3OVl9LM

Click here to watch more: https://www.sonyliv.com/sports/cricket-indian-street-premier-league-1700001390

Click here to subscribe now: https://bit.ly/3Q78rHU

Watch the highlights of the inaugural match between Sachin Tendulkar's Master 11 and Akshay Kumar's Khiladi 11 in the Indian Street Premier League 2024. Sachin Tendulkar's Master 11 scored 94 runs in 10 overs and lost 7 wickets in the process. Sachin was the top scorer with 30 runs. Akshay Kumar's Khiladi 11 then put up a strong performance during the chase but lost the match by 5 runs in the end. 

Master 11: Sachin Tendulkar, Amir, Suresh Raina, Yusuf Pathan, Stuart Binny, Rishabh Chavan, Munaf Patel, Ram Charan, Kunal Khemmu, Samir Kochhar, Elvish Yadav.

Khiladi 11: Akshay Kumar, Suriya, Irfan Pathan, Robin Uthappa, Praveen Kumar, Naman Ojha, Gaurav Taneja, Prateik Babbar, Sukhwinder Singh, Munawar Farooqui, Riyaz Ali.

snippet.title: Aar Ya Paar In Haridwar - Stand-up Comedy By Sundeep Sharma
snippet.description:
It's a nostalgic story from my teenage years. Young and stupid make the interesting story tellers later in life. I hope I am not wrong. This video is about my Haridwar visit with my parents and siblings and my teenage bravado. I have performed this bit for a few years, I am hoping that you like it. Please do share this video and subscribe to my channel. Do leave a comment :) 

Credits: 
Venue courtesy: The Habitat-Comedy and Music Cafe
Directed by: Balraj Ghai
Edited by: Ankit
Shot by: Dishang Popat, Vivian Castelino Harsh Shah and Karan Kundnani
Live sound recording: Yash Rajiv Barse, Siegen Moopnar
Sound mixing and mastering: Sreejith Menon
Written and performed by: Sundeep Sharma 

Special Thanks: Pictures and video footage of Haridwar: Garima Lohumi
Sonam Priya for inputs
Emina Singh for the quote in the beginning and being a patient ear
Saurabh Pandey for being the constant support
My babies Alpha and Beta for being the reason I work and go to work like Papa Bear.
&
My Mother for being the constant support and playing a character in my story here. 
My Father for being the man he was and always inspiring me to do better and never give up. 


Follow me on:

Instagram:
https://www.instagram.com/sundeep.sharma/

Facebook:
https://www.facebook.com/Sundeepshawarma/

X:
https://twitter.com/sundeepshawarma

13:04 Boot Space
13:58 3rd Rows seats space and amenities

snippet.description:
Little did I know there was a surprise ü§∞ Baby Shower coming up for me. 
I have always seen and enjoyed watching baby showers through videos. But this was one of the best and the most memorable days of my life. 
Mastermind or the planner was Jeema, a kind-hearted follower of mine who turned out to be a very dear and close friend. Coordinated with the rest of my friends. Her cute home-baked mommy Cake. I didn‚Äôt want to cut it as it was too cute to look at. And her son Jain who joined was a silent partner ‚ô•Ô∏è
Nifla, as usual with her amazing food and drinks. Shilja with her home-baked brownies which I couldn‚Äôt get a photo of as it got over soon. Sneha, Naina, and Shilja with their lovely gift from Victoria‚Äôs Secret.

It was such a surprise cum shock to see this coming. I can‚Äôt get over it as I am still in the shower mode üòÉ‚Ä¶.
Thank you my dear ladies for this cute sweet and most memorable day in my life. I will cherish this forever üòçüòçüòçüòç

@niflaub @naina170390 @menon3020 @shiljavinay & Jeema ‚ô•Ô∏è

Little did I know there was a surprise ü§∞ Baby Shower coming up for me. 
I have always seen and enjoyed watching baby showers through videos. But this was one of the best and the most memorable days of my life. 
Mastermind or the planner was Jeema, a kind-hearted follower of mine who turned out to be a very dear and close friend. Coordinated with the rest of my friends. Her cute home-baked mommy Cake. I didn‚Äôt want to cut it as it was too cute to look at. And her son Jain who joined was a silent partner ‚ô•Ô∏è
Nifla, as usual with her amazing food and drinks. Shilja with her home-baked brownies which I couldn‚Äôt get a photo of as it got over soon. Sneha, Naina, and Shilja with their lovely gift from Victoria‚Äôs Secret.

It was such a surprise cum shock to see this coming. I can‚Äôt get over it as I am still in the shower mode üòÉ‚Ä¶.
Thank you my dear ladies for this cute sweet and most memorable day in my life. I will cherish this forever üòçüòçüòçüòç

snippet.title: Maha Shivarathri Special rangoli designs 2024 || Simple Pandaga muggulu || easy Festival kolam
snippet.description:
Maha Shivarathri Special rangoli designs 2024 || Simple Pandaga muggulu || easy Festival kolam
It is our tradition to draw kolam every day morning at the doorsteps.
There are many benefits of drawing kolam in front of the house.
It is auspicious and believes Goddess Lakshmi enters the house if kolam is drawn.
Kolam brings a lot of positive vibrations and energy to you and your home.
Draw kolam soon after you wake up and then do your prayers.
Kolam or rangoli ( ‡§∞‡§Ç‡§ó‡•ã‡§≤‡•Ä  ) is a part of Indian culture and transferred from generation to the next generation.
This ancient art form is also called as muggulu in parts of South India like Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.
People draw different creative rangoli kolam designs using kolam powder or muggu pindi which is 
actually crushed Lime stone powder available in different parts of India.
There are different types of rangoli or kolam designs like dots kolam, sikku kolam, padi kolam, Margazhi kolam.
People draw special rangoli designs for Festivals like Sankranthi (Pongal), Diwali (Deepavali), Vijaya Dashami (Dasara).
Women create deepam rangoli or kolam designs during Diwali festival time, create very big and Dhanurmasam muggulu (Margazhi) for Sankranthi or Pongal festival.
It is a belief among the people that drawing muggulu in front of the house in the early morning soon after wake brings
good fortune to them and their family.
People mix rice flour to limestone powder and prepare their own kolam powder. Muggulu can also be drawn with rice flour only.
These Beautiful and creative designs are decorated with flowers based on the occasion or festival.

Maha Shivarathri Special rangoli designs 2024 || Simple Pandaga muggulu || easy Festival kolam
It is our tradition to draw kolam every day morning at the doorsteps.
There are many benefits of drawing kolam in front of the house.
It is auspicious and believes Goddess Lakshmi enters the house if kolam is drawn.
Kolam brings a lot of positive vibrations and energy to you and your home.
Draw kolam soon after you wake up and then do your prayers.
Kolam or rangoli ( ‡§∞‡§Ç‡§ó‡•ã‡§≤‡•Ä  ) is a part of Indian culture and transferred from generation to the next generation.
This ancient art form is also called as muggulu in parts of South India like Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.
People draw different creative rangoli kolam designs using kolam powder or muggu pindi which is 
actually crushed Lime stone powder available in different parts of India.
There are different types of rangoli or kolam designs like dots kolam, sikku kolam, padi kolam, Margazhi kolam.
People draw special rangoli designs for Festivals like Sankranthi (Pongal), Diwali (Deepavali), Vijaya Dashami (Dasara).
Women create deepam rangoli or kolam designs during Diwali festival time, create very big and Dhanurmasam muggulu (Margazhi) for Sankranthi or Pongal festival.
It is a belief among the people that drawing muggulu in front of the house in the early morning soon after wake brings
good fortune to them and their family.
People mix rice flour to limestone powder and prepare their own kolam powder. Muggulu can also be drawn with rice flour only.
These Beautiful and creative designs are decorated with flowers based on the occasion or festival.
The following types of video tutorials for rangoli and kolam designs with dots and freehand are shown in a very easy step by procedure in #easyrangoli channel

snippet.title: GOAT BLOOD FRY | Traditional Goat Blood Recipe Cooking In Village | Goat Blood Gravy with Intestine
snippet.description:
Today in our village, We cook our village's traditional goat blood recipe by making blood gravy and blood fry. We call this recipe as "Raththa Koottu" and "Raththa Poriyal". We add some goat internal parts to goat blood gravy, such as the liver, lungs, and intestine.

Finally, we enjoy the food with our favourite muttun curry! The taste is delicious!

Episode 4026: Important Sting Operation
--------------------------------------------------------
Taarak contacts Popatlal's boss, growing concerned upon learning he's also unavailable. The Gokuldham residents assume Popatlal might be immersed in a crucial sting operation. Meanwhile, Popatlal yearns for his Gokuldham family. Later, he receives a summons for an important sting operation at the office. Now, the challenge for Popatlal is to leave the office unnoticed for the covert mission.

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: Khaie Episode 24 - [Eng Sub] - Digitally Presented by Sparx Smartphones - 7th March 2024
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Khaie Episode 24 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Sparx Smartphones - Faysal Quraishi - Durefishan Saleem - 7th March 2024 - Har Pal Geo

Khaie Digitally Presented by Sparx Smartphones #shinewithsparx
Get Ready to be Enthralled by 'Khaie' - Brought to You by Geo TV with the Cutting-Edge Innovation of Sparx Smartphone as the Exclusive Digital Presenting Partner. A Spectacular Journey Awaits

The story is a revenge saga that unfolds against the backdrop of the ancient tradition of Khaie, where the male members of an enemy's family are eliminated to stop the continuation of their lineage.  At the center of this age-old vendetta are Darwesh Khan, Duraab Khan, and his son Channar Khan, with Zamdaa, the daughter of Darwesh, bearing the heaviest consequences.  
Darwesh Khan is haunted by his father's murder at the hands of Duraab Khan. Seeking a peaceful life, Darwesh aims to broker a truce to end generational enmity. However, suspicions arise, and Duraab Khan and his son Channar Khan doubt Darwesh's intentions for peace.
Despite the genuine efforts of Darwesh, a kind-hearted man with a message for peace, a tragic turn of events unfolds during a celebration at Darwesh's home, causing immense suffering for Zamdaa and her family.
Will Zamdaa bow down in front of her enemies? If not, then will Zamdaa be able to take revenge on her family culprits? Will Zamdaa find allies in her journey, or will she face her enemies alone?

Written By: Saqlain Abbas
Directed By: Syed Wajahat Hussain
Produced By: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi
Production House: 7th Sky Entertainment

Cast:
Faysal Quraishi as Channar Khan
Durefishan Saleem as Zamdaa
Khalid Butt as Duraab Khan 
Noor ul Hassan as Darwesh

PM Modi Kashmir Video: Prime Minister Narendra Modi today gave a gift of about Rs 6400 crore to Kashmir. Thousands of Kashmiris arrived to attend the PM's rally. Meanwhile, PM Modi spoke to the Nazim of Pulwama. The video of Nazim-Modi's conversation is going viral. While addressing the rally at Bakshi Stadium in Srinagar, the Prime Minister said that Jammu and Kashmir is touching new heights of development today. He said that this happened after the removal of 370. Targeting the opposition, the PM said that for decades Congress and its allies misled Jammu and Kashmir and the country in the name of 370.

PM Modi Kashmir Video: Prime Minister Narendra Modi today gave a gift of about Rs 6400 crore to Kashmir. Thousands of Kashmiris arrived to attend the PM's rally. Meanwhile, PM Modi spoke to the Nazim of Pulwama. The video of Nazim-Modi's conversation is going viral. While addressing the rally at Bakshi Stadium in Srinagar, the Prime Minister said that Jammu and Kashmir is touching new heights of development today. He said that this happened after the removal of 370. Targeting the opposition, the PM said that for decades Congress and its allies misled Jammu and Kashmir and the country in the name of 370.

Episode 4025: Birthday Ke Din Gayab
--------------------------------------------------------
Bhide posts a birthday message for Popatlal on the society board. Concerned about Popatlal's unavailability, everyone attempts to reach him without success and turns to Abdul for information. Sodhi and Bhide, eager to celebrate, make party plans, unaware that Champaklal overhears their conversation.

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.
